comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T22:00:29.132Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: pm-e9zh owns terminal resolution evidence and completed audits inspected history,but no open task owns typed terminal relationship reconstruction in changelog-safe epoch batches; this task is downstream and coordinated,not duplicate."
body: "## Epoch ordering\n\nWork newest-to-oldest within stable lineages so current conventions inform, but do not overwrite, historical semantics. Suggested epochs: current release train; post-package architecture; SDK and extension expansion; early CLI and storage foundation; imported or legacy archives.\n\n## Evidence hierarchy\n\nExplicit item IDs and immutable mutation events outrank inferred title similarity. Linked commits, PRs, releases, tests, files, and docs provide provenance. Textual resemblance is only a candidate signal. Canceled experiments and superseded decisions remain visible and are not treated as outstanding work.\n\n## Changelog boundary\n\nTerminal metadata updates can move items into current generated changelog sections. Each bounded batch owns its final tracker mutation, package-owned changelog regeneration and check, diff review, and evidence comment as one atomic handoff."
